## Investigation Complete

**Issue**: #751 — Main CI red: Deploy to staging
**Type**: BUG

### Assessment

| Metric | Value | Reasoning |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| Severity | HIGH | Blocks all deployments on every main push |
| Complexity | LOW | Single GitHub secret rotation; no code changes needed |
| Confidence | HIGH | CI log is unambiguous: "RAILWAY_TOKEN is invalid or expired: Not Authorized" |

### Key Findings

**Root cause**: `RAILWAY_TOKEN` GitHub secret is expired. Railway API returns `Not Authorized` at the "Validate Railway secrets" step in `staging-pipeline.yml:49-58`.

**Why previous "fixes" failed**: PRs #749 and #750 (and #740, #741 before them) only created documentation files claiming to have rotated the token. None actually ran `gh secret set`. The archon agent cannot create Railway API tokens — the `apiTokenCreate` GraphQL mutation returns "Not Authorized" when called with the CLI's OAuth access token (I verified this directly).

**This requires manual human action**: Alex must go to https://railway.com/account/tokens, create a new no-expiry token, and run `gh secret set RAILWAY_TOKEN --repo alexsiri7/reli`.

